# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Once your real domain is set up, uncomment and edit ONE of the two lines
# below to force a single canonical version (pick www OR non-www — not both).
# This matters for SEO: Google treats www and non-www as different sites
# unless you redirect one to the other.
#
# Redirect www -> apex (matches the canonical/og:url tags already set on your pages):
https://www.artisband.ro/* https://artisband.ro/:splat 301
#
# OR, if you'd rather use www as the canonical version instead, comment the
# line above and uncomment this one (and update the canonical tags in
# index.html/about.html to match):
# https://artisband.ro/* https://www.artisband.ro/:splat 301
